cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.NE

The paper focuses on efficient sampling for text-to-speech synthesis using neural networks. This falls under the general category of signal processing and machine learning, which suggests cs.SD (Sound) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks and weight pruning techniques, which are common in natural language processing and machine learning, respectively. This suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new generation scheme for increasing sampling efficiency, which falls under the category of neural network optimization and could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
